description: From Middle English belouken, bilouken, from Old English belūcan (“to lock up, bring to an end”), equivalent to be- +‎ lock.

verbs.description: belock (third-person singular simple present belocks, present participle belocking, simple past and past participle belocked)

entries.meaning: (archaic, transitive) To lock up or lock in place; hold tight; fasten.
